---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTABlock from '../../components/CTABlock.astro';
import BlogHero from '../../components/BlogHero.astro';
import BlogFigure from '../../components/BlogFigure.astro';
import RelatedPosts from '../../components/RelatedPosts.astro';
import { business, BASE } from '../../data/business';
import { postBySlug, postsBySlugs, RELATED_POSTS } from '../../data/posts';

const post = postBySlug('kilmarnock-bathroom-suite-strip-out')!;
const relatedPosts = postsBySlugs(RELATED_POSTS[post.slug] ?? []).slice(0, 3);
const siteUrl = business.siteUrl.replace(/\/$/, '');
const url = `${siteUrl}/blog/${post.slug}/`;
const ogImage = `${siteUrl}${BASE}/gallery/kilmarnock-bathroom-suite-plumbing-02-1600w.jpg`;

const articleSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  '@id': `${url}#article`,
  headline: post.title,
  description: post.description,
  inLanguage: 'en-GB',
  datePublished: post.date,
  dateModified: post.date,
  author: { '@type': 'Person', name: post.author, worksFor: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` } },
  publisher: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  image: [ogImage],
  mainEntityOfPage: url,
  keywords: [post.keyword],
  wordCount: post.wordCount,
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`${post.title} | Sorn Handyman Services`}
  description={post.description}
  canonicalPath={`/blog/${post.slug}/`}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  ogType="article"
  extraSchema={articleSchema}
>
  <Breadcrumbs trail={[
    { name: 'Home', href: `${BASE}/` },
    { name: 'Blog', href: `${BASE}/blog/` },
    { name: post.title },
  ]} />

  <article class="container-x py-10 lg:py-14 max-w-3xl">
    <header>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-amber-600">
        <span>{post.area}</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <span class="text-navy-900/60">{post.readMinutes} min read</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <time datetime={post.date} class="text-navy-900/60">{post.dateDisplay}</time>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-navy-900 leading-tight">
        {post.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-navy-900/75">
        A bathroom job in Kilmarnock that turned into a bigger one once the suite
        came out. The old pipework was leaking, the floor was soft underneath, and
        the timber had started to rot. We stripped it back to the joists before
        anything new went in.
      </p>
    </header>

    <BlogHero slug="kilmarnock-bathroom-suite-plumbing-02" />

    <div class="prose-sorn mt-8 text-lg cv-auto">
      <h2>What the job involved</h2>
      <p>
        The suite came out first — bath, basin, WC and vanity — so we could see
        what was going on underneath. As soon as the floor covering lifted, the
        scale of the hidden damage was obvious. The copper feeds under the bath
        had a slow weep that had been running long enough to blacken the boards.
      </p>
      <p>
        We replaced the leaking pipework, pulled up the rotten flooring and
        renewed the timber back to sound joists. Only then did the room get put
        back — new boards, fresh fixings, clean pipe runs and the suite reset
        square. It is not glamorous work but it is the difference between a
        finish that lasts and a finish that hides another leak.
      </p>

      <BlogFigure slug="kilmarnock-bathroom-suite-plumbing-02" />

      <h2>Things to think about before you start</h2>
      <p>
        Soft-feeling floorboards at the bath or WC, a musty smell, or a ceiling
        stain on the room below are the three signs a bathroom has hidden pipe
        damage. Any one of them is worth a look before you commit to a new
        suite, because fitting new ware onto wet timber only buys you a year or
        two.
      </p>
      <p>
        Plan for the possibility that the floor will need work. Budget for a
        couple of extra hours, and agree with your fitter up front what happens
        if the boards need replacing once the suite is out. Honest conversations
        on day one save arguments on day three.
      </p>

      <p>
        If you are in Kilmarnock and need something similar, Fraser will come
        and look for free. Call <strong>07900 255876</strong> or WhatsApp
        <strong>+44 7472 223323</strong>. FREE no-obligation quote, every job
        priced individually.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-navy-900/10 bg-navy-50/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-navy-900/60">Written by</p>
        <p class="mt-1 font-serif text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">{post.author}</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-navy-900/75 text-sm">{post.authorBio}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  {relatedPosts.length > 0 && (
    <RelatedPosts posts={relatedPosts} eyebrow="Keep reading" heading="Related posts" variant="tinted" />
  )}

  <CTABlock
    heading="Bathroom starting to show its age?"
    sub="Send a couple of photos over WhatsApp and Fraser will come and look for free."
    location="Kilmarnock"
  />
</BaseLayout>
